  <front>
   <head>Reply to the foregoing Verses.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">did I hope to make your Anguish less?</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I try'd to cure, and I have caught, Distress.</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Suppress your Sighs, dry up your Tears; 'tis Time:</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Excess of Virtue may become a Crime.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">You lost, you say, a Friend, and Father too;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But know, Mankind would lose a Friend in you.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
